Electronic loogbok with data calculator for ship engineers

There is existing app elcalc (see folder)

Elcalc is going to be only function of bigger application. 
We will continue design from elcalc which is clear and easy to use.

First we need to create new main page called logbook

Loogbok is place where engineer (user) is going to place values from flowmeters, running hours of devices, fuel ROB (remain on board etc)

General overviev of graphical interface.

There is main display with input card.
Input card is always visible and ready to recieve input from physical values (user input)

Input card values that user input.
ID - automaticaly added unique number. It cannot be changed. Every input have ID+1 value  (input 17 - ID 17, input 123 - ID 123 etc)
DATE DD:MM:YY
TIME HH:MM  (time can be input in following example  01:06, 02:12 16:24  - means 6 minutes separation. it will be used in further calculations.)
EVENT  have to be chosen from list  NOON, STBY, EOSP, SOSP, FWE, ARRIVAL, DEPARTURE, SHIFTING-BEG, SHIFTING-END, MID
PLACE can be manual input like EMDEN, GDYNIA or any city name BUT There have to be two constant inputs that can be chosen from list SCRUBBER OL-CL, SCRUBBER CL-OL
ME REV C        engine rpm counter [rpm] (revolutions per MINUTE)
